RTCIceCandidateTcpType.summary: The interface's read-only tcpType property is included on TCP candidates to provide additional details about the candidate type.

remarks.para:
The tcpType field's value is set from the candidateInfo options object passed to the constructor.
You can't specify the value of tcpType directly in the options object, but its value is automatically extracted from the object's candidate a-line, if it's formatted properly.

RTCIceCandidateTcpType.value: If the is "tcp", tcpType has one of the following values:tcpType is null for UDP candidates.
